(37, '2011-08-21 16:15:57', 'For my MEng project I studied Impact Dynamics, and I hypothesized that you could approximate Impact Dynamics for a solid Media with a system of springs and point masses.  Attached is my write-up, and I also interestingly found that if you let the system relax to a steady state that the method which I like to call Gershon Mechanics, can approximate static systems as well as dynamic systems.  The method is also inherently non-linear for large deformation.', 'Approximating Solid Media Impact Dynamics with a System of Point Masses and Springs.pdf', 1, '/files/Engineering/Mechanical Engineering/Dynamics/Impact Dynamics/Impact v1.0', NULL, 0),
