(480, '2013-01-25 15:10:22', 'the chain would spin the piston barrel portion of the bent axis pump which would deliver fluid to the gerotor which in turns spins the hub. The plate which the pistons run on can have a variable pitch to pump more or less fluid depending on how fast you are going. The gerotor works like a wankel rotary engine, it follows an eccentric path within the housing to turn the sun gear. Its a cool solution, but for simplicity sake im going to replace the gerotor with a more basic design.\r\n\r\nI think the best solution to get your design to turn is using the same principles as the nuvinci or the torroidal CVT which rely on forcing oil between the bearing surfaces. Kinda tricky but is already proven and would be the lighter of the 2 designs (i think). we should get a product definition together.', '', 62, '/files/Engineering/Mechanical Engineering/CVT EWTG', 0, 0),
