(1495, '2014-02-05 20:36:03', 'From ERIC ANDERS of OSE:\r\n\r\n Enclosed is an explanation from the client of the phone case project I talked to you about last week. Basically, we will be starting out with a phone case for a Samsung Galaxy phone. It will be a standard case with a clear back Panel and secondary Inner back panel. In the space between the panels the user can add charms. The secondary panel will either be a stamped metal part with different designs stamped into it or injection molded plastic panels plated to look like metal. I am thinking we probably injection mold the case out of clear plastic and just paint or do in mold decoration over the areas we want a solid color. That way we dont have to make a separate transparent back wall and assemble them together. I also discussed with them that I think it would be better to install the snap in inner back panel from inside the case after removing the phone rather than having a hinged door on top of the case. This will cut down on the complexity and number of parts required. I have downloaded quite a few different Phone models and phone case models form Grab Cad so I am thinking we could probably save some time starting with one of those. The customer is also sending me a sample Phone so we can be sure whatever models we do build to are accurate. \r\n\r\n                Can you have your mechanical guys give me an idea what they would charge for this? If the number works we can have a conference call with them to go over the project and discuss the details.', '', 1, '/files/Business/Paradigm Motion/Products/Customer Product/OSE Product Dev/Phone Case', 0, 0),
