(1615, '2014-03-16 15:19:30', 'There''s something about gravity that can repel.  Boiling water as a metaphor.  What I saw in a pot of boiling water was some bubbles which formed and were attracted to other bubbles similar to gravity.  But there were cases which the surface tension shape or whatever the causing force was to push the bubbles away.  It seemed that the bubbles and bubble clusters that caused repulsion had a correlation to size.  The idea here is to develop a formulation of the law of gravity which as a function of particle size and spacing actually causes a repulsive force.', '', 1, '/files/Physics/G-LOG', 0, 0),
