(3934, '2015-12-27 16:25:27', 'The picture below is what I am talking about, where a shoppers path is calculated with search algorithms similar to the way google maps calculates directions for a road trip.<br /><br />\n\nThis software technology exists and could fairly easily be adapted for this solution.<br /><br />\n\nYou may be wondering how the app knows where everything is, well as the app begins to grow in popularity, a google type street view mapper could roam stores indexing all the absolute positions of all the product.\n<br /><br />\nWhere prior to the robot mapping systems the app database would be developed locally and with store collaboration maps would be made and item location algorithms would be developed with manual walkthroughs with photographs. The algorithms then stick the images together and product item locations are indexed by pulling from the image data. Then if the manual walk through images are mapped successfully with the software, then the robot mappers taking pictures should not have a problem getting the store data.', 'image.jpeg', 1, '/files/Invention Ideas/Shop Assistant', 67818, 0),
